docs.abstract: The image, shared on Twitter by Representative Paul Gosar of Arizona, is photoshopped and has been circulating online for years.
docs.snippet: The image, shared on Twitter by Representative Paul Gosar of Arizona, is photoshopped and has been circulating online for years.
docs.lead_paragraph: False. As lawmakers in Washington and allies around the world grappled with President Trump’s decision to launch a strike that killed Iran’s most important general, an Arizona Republican, Representative Paul Gosar, shared a fake image from his personal Twitter account on Monday purporting to show President Barack Obama shaking hands with President Hassan Rouhani of Iran. The two men have never met in person.

headline.main: Republican Congressman Shares Fake Image of Obama and Iranian President

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An official letter from the Defense Department informing Iraq that the United States was “repositioning forces” for “movement out of Iraq” produced headlines around the world that an American withdrawal had begun.

headline.main: The U.S. Seemed to Be Leaving Iraq. But It Was All an ‘Honest Mistake.’
